<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-21T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-21T14:00:00-05:00" n="507" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d507">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.1431/164: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">O’Donoghue</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-21T14:00:00-05:00">March 21, 1936—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>16. Referring to the Legation’s telegram No. 23, March 18, noon.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>If Guatemala insists on insertion the Department prefers that “by
                                exporter” be replaced by “made in the country of export.”</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>Language quoted appears acceptable except that use of word
                                “special” has restrictive connotation hence the Department would
                                like to have it omitted or replaced by “other”.</item>
                            <label>3.</label>
                            <item>The Department hopes to have texts ready for submission to you by
                                airmail next week.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>